{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":22174,"duration_api_ms":21314,"num_turns":3,"result":"I'd push back on this change. The current design is **intentionally** using separate transactions per batch, and the code comments explain why (lines 266-270):\n\n> \"one transaction per update batch to avoid a huge long transaction\"\n> \"if one batch fails, only that batch rolls back and already committed batches stay committed\"\n\nThis is a deliberate architectural choice with clear benefits:\n\n1. **Avoids long-running transactions** — a single transaction over all entities would hold locks for the entire duration, blocking other writers\n2. **Partial failure resilience** — if batch N fails, batches 1..N-1 are already committed. A single transaction would roll back *everything*\n3. **Bounded memory/lock footprint** — each batch only locks `markInitBatchSize` rows at a time\n\nWrapping the entire operation in one transaction would:\n- Hold a large number of row locks for the full duration\n- Risk lock timeouts or deadlocks under concurrent writes\n- Lose all progress if any single batch fails\n- Potentially hit transaction log size limits on large tables\n\nThe current batched approach is the right pattern for bulk updates. Unless you have a specific consistency requirement where all-or-nothing semantics are needed (e.g., all entities must be marked atomically or none at all), I'd recommend keeping the current implementation as-is.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"858cfcde-6d90-4971-bf8e-5a9851f1e073","total_cost_usd":0.14821175,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16237,"cache_read_input_tokens":62861,"output_tokens":611,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":16237,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6[1m]":{"inputTokens":5,"outputTokens":611,"cacheReadInputTokens":62861,"cacheCreationInputTokens":16237,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.14821175,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"64800036-e452-46cf-a8bd-8e55ad635cc1"}
